com.googlecode.aluminumproject.libraries
Class LibraryInformation

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.aluminumproject.libraries.LibraryInformation

public class LibraryInformation
extends Object

Information about a Library.

An important piece of information is the library URL, which, together with the library version, should be globally unique. The preferred way of making sure that a library URL is unique is by choosing a host name that is owned by the library creator.

Another library information aspect is whether or not the library supports dynamic actions.

getVersionedUrl

public String getVersionedUrl()
Returns a combination of the URL and the version of the library. As an example: if the library URL is http://aluminumproject.googlecode.com/core and the library has version 1.0, then the versioned library URL will be http://aluminumproject.googlecode.com/core/1.0.

Returns:
the library URL, with the library version appended to it
